The Move On Forward show Photo: Courtesy of Da Sheng A new variety show has captured the attention of audiences by focusing on people who have recently suffered a breakup. The first episode of the series Move On Forward, or Canlande Qianxing, was released on Chinese streaming site Tencent Video on Wednesday.Featuring six young people who lost love and five stars as their company, the show followed each of their stories and raised many questions about romance. The show aims to provide the power of healing to guide young people on how to examine their own emotional wounds and find the right way to move on.  Sharing is a way to heal and represents the warm feelings and encouragement from strangers. Additionally, Chinese stars like Zheng Kai, Rainie Yang, Qiao Xin and Chen Ming appeared on the show to provide their own perspectives.